# Current Goal

**Goal:** Containerized Runtime  
**Summary:** Origami is a graph-based agentic circuit framework. The API is stabilized (90 contracts complete). The goal is now a containerized, product-agnostic runtime: the engine validates circuit topology, processes `map[string]any` artifacts, fetches domain data over MCP via `MCPRemoteFS`, and deploys as a 4-service OCI topology (Gateway, Engine, Knowledge, Domain). Product repos (Asterisk, Achilles) provide pure config/data — zero Go. `origami fold` is the universal compiler from YAML manifest to running containers.

## Open Checklist

- [x] Domain data externalized — all product data in Asterisk `internal/`, served over MCP via `domainserve`
- [x] `MCPRemoteFS` + `domainserve` library — virtual filesystem over MCP, domain server as a reusable package
- [x] `origami fold` domain-serve codegen — generates domain-serve binary from `domain_serve:` YAML manifest
- [x] `map[string]any` artifact processing — typed artifact structs deleted, generic extractors in place
- [x] Calibration harness decoupled — `calibrate.Run()` with `ScenarioLoader`/`CaseCollector`/`ReportRenderer`
- [x] 4-service deploy configs — docker-compose + K8s manifests for Gateway, Engine, Knowledge, Asterisk (DSC P6)
- [x] Domain-separation final validation — full circuit E2E through containerized stack (DSC P7)
- [x] Topology validation at load time — `topology:` field enforced with graph-shape + cardinality checks
- [x] Schematic runtime toolkit — generic patterns extracted from `schematics/rca/` to `schematics/toolkit/`
- [x] Ingestion pipeline decoupled — generic `ingest.Run()` ETL harness; RCA/RP becomes an adapter
- [x] Monolith retired — fold-generated monolith binary replaced by test wrappers + MCP tools; fold generates only domain-serve
- [x] Framework API layered — root package documented with `doc.go` and category headers, 26 dead exports cleaned
- [x] Root `README.md` positions Origami as a standalone framework

